<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- All key-sig notes (B, E, A) marked accid.ges="f" throughout. C major chords use
  natural E (C E G) — these do NOT get accid.ges="f" since E natural is needed.
  Fm uses Ab = A accid.ges="f". Cm uses Eb = E accid.ges="f".
- Phrase 1+2 (mm. 1-8): 4-note LH quarter chords with Eb, C, Bb cycling.
  Phrase 2 RH moves to higher register (Eb5, G5, Bb5) for subtle growth.
  Eb "333" Δ in m.5 (Eb2 G2 Bb2 D3) — richer tonic for second phrase.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 9-12): G#° substituted with Cm (viio → vi°). RH reaches highest
  notes in arrangement (G5 Bb5 in m.9 beat 3). Descending RH line E5→D5→C5→Bb4 in
  m.11 provides stepwise contrary counterpoint to melody's C5→Bb4→Ab4→G4 descent.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 13-16): Cm → Bb → Eb sequence in LH. 3-note RH chord in m.13
  (Bb4 Eb5 G5) is fullest RH texture. Bb "42" sus4 approach in m.15 RH (D4 F4 Bb4).
  Final Eb whole note in all registers (RH G4 Bb4 Eb5, LH Eb2 Bb2 Eb3 G3).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m.11: RH descending single-note line E5→D5→C5→Bb4 against melody's parallel descent.
  Inner voice contrary motion: LH bass C2→Bb2→C2→Eb2.
- m.9 climax: RH reaches G5 Bb5 (highest register), LH supports with full Eb/Bb chords.
- Pickup m.0: 2-note RH (G4 Bb4) previews the Eb tonic. Bass Eb2 established immediately.
- m.15: 3-note RH Bb chord (D4 F4 Bb4) — dominant pre-cadential swell before final Eb.
- C major chords (III in Eb) used throughout for color — the "picardian" major III gives
  brightness in an otherwise flat-heavy tonality.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup + mm. 1-4: Quarter-chord LH, 2-note RH, steady 4/4. Establishes Eb key.
- mm. 5-8: RH climbs to higher octave; Eb Δ7 LH in m.5 adds warmth.
- mm. 9-12: Highest RH register (G5 Bb5); most harmonic activity (4 chords/bar in m.9).
  Followed by stepwise descent and settling in mm. 10-12.
- mm. 13-16: Cm → Bb → Eb final motion; LH full 4-note chords; RH 3-note at m.13.
  Final Eb whole note root position in all voices — complete, settled resolution.
-->
